default The following taxes are proposed for devolution 
defaultin their entirety or to contain a financial element to be retained locally.
defaultCouncil Tax
defaultWe call for the imm
defaultediate removal of Council Tax referendum limits. Local authorities know the needs of their areas and should be free 
defaultto 
defaultdetermine their own Council Tax levels having regard to their existing democratic mandates. T
defaulthe 
defaultnew 
defaultcontrol
defaults 
defaultover levies 
defaultthat are limiting the capacity of Combined Authorities to raise funding for infrastructure developments should also be removed and in the longer term successful Combined Authorities should be given precepting powers.
defaultCouncil Tax itself is in need of urgent
default reform. The 
defaultcurrent property bandings are more than twenty years out of date and a
defaultrrangements need to be put in place 
defaultnow 
defaultfor 
defaultgeneral
default revaluation
default. The structure and number of C
defaultouncil 
defaultT
defaultax bands should be reviewed at the same time.
default 
defaultOur ambition is that Coun
defaultcil Tax be developed as a fully localised tax and that the setting and adjustment of bandings should be done by Combined Authorities. We acknowledge that there will be complications in the first instance in this regard, but we would be willing to work with
default Government to make this change. The offer in return for th
defaultis devolution is that retained Council T
defaultax will be used to drive growth and increase prosperity and wellbeing in local areas, better 
defaultmeeting
